msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:filterverticesbyz``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3183
msgid "Fix geometries"
msgstr "Correction des géométries"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3184
msgid ""
"Attempts to create a valid representation of a given invalid geometry "
"without losing any of the input vertices. Already valid geometries are "
"returned without further intervention. Always outputs multi-geometry layer."
msgstr ""
"Tente de créer une représentation valide d'une géométrie non valide donnée "
"sans perdre aucun des vertex d'entrée. Les géométries déjà valides sont "
"retournées sans autre intervention. Produit toujours une couche multi-"
"géométrie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3189
msgid ""
"|checkbox| Allows :ref:`features in-place modification "
"<processing_inplace_edit>` of point, line, and polygon features without M "
"enabled"
msgstr ""
"|checkbox| Permet :ref:`la modification de la couche source "
"<processing_inplace_edit>` pour des entités de type point, ligne ou polygone"
" sans valeurs M"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3193
msgid "M values will be dropped from the output."
msgstr "Les valeurs M seront supprimées de la sortie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3213
msgid "**Repair method**"
msgstr "**Méthode de réparation**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3218
msgid "Method used to repair the geometries. One of:"
msgstr "Méthode utilisée pour réparer les géométries :"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3229
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3252
msgid "**Fixed geometries**"
msgstr "**Corrections des geeométries**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3255
msgid "The output vector layer with fixed geometries."
msgstr "La couche vectorielle de sortie avec les géométries corrigees."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3260
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:fixgeometries``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:fixgeometries``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3270
msgid "Force right-hand-rule"
msgstr "Forcer la règle de droite"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3272
msgid ""
"Forces polygon geometries to respect the Right-Hand-Rule, in which the area "
"that is bounded by a polygon is to the right of the boundary. In particular,"
" the exterior ring is oriented in a clockwise direction and any interior "
"rings in a counter-clockwise direction."
msgstr ""
"Force les géométries de polygone à respecter la règle de droite, dans "
"laquelle la zone délimitée par un polygone se trouve à droite de la limite. "
"En particulier, l'anneau extérieur est orienté dans le sens horaire et tous "
"les anneaux intérieurs dans le sens antihoraire."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3297
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3320
msgid "**Reoriented**"
msgstr "**Réorienté**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3323
msgid "The output vector layer with reoriented geometries."
msgstr "Couche vectorielle de sortie avec des géométries réorientées."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3328
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:forcerhr``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:forcerhr``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3338
msgid "Geodesic line split at antimeridian"
msgstr "Ligne géodésique divisée à l'antiméridien"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3340
msgid ""
"Splits a line into multiple geodesic segments, whenever the line crosses the"
" antimeridian (±180 degrees longitude)."
msgstr ""
"Fractionne une ligne en plusieurs segments géodésiques, chaque fois que la "
"ligne traverse l'antiméridien (± 180 degrés de longitude)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3343
msgid ""
"Splitting at the antimeridian helps the visual display of the lines in some "
"projections. The returned geometry will always be a multi-part geometry."
msgstr ""
"La division à l'antiméridien aide à l'affichage visuel des lignes dans "
"certaines projections. La géométrie renvoyée sera toujours une géométrie en "
"plusieurs parties."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3347
msgid ""
"Whenever line segments in the input geometry cross the antimeridian, they "
"will be split into two segments, with the latitude of the breakpoint being "
"determined using a geodesic line connecting the points either side of this "
"segment. The current project ellipsoid setting will be used when calculating"
" this breakpoint."
msgstr ""
"Chaque fois que des segments de ligne dans la géométrie d'entrée traversent "
"l'antiméridien, ils seront divisés en deux segments, la latitude du point "
"d'arrêt étant déterminée à l'aide d'une ligne géodésique reliant les points "
"de chaque côté de ce segment. Le paramètre ellipsoïde du projet actuel sera "
"utilisé lors du calcul de ce point d'arrêt."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3354
msgid ""
"If the input geometry contains M or Z values, these will be linearly "
"interpolated for the new vertices created at the antimeridian."
msgstr ""
"Si la géométrie d'entrée contient des valeurs M ou Z, celles-ci seront "
"interpolées linéairement pour les nouveaux sommets créés à l'antiméridien."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3380
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3403
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6786
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6811
msgid "**Split**"
msgstr "**Fractionner**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3406
msgid "The output line vector layer split at the antimeridian."
msgstr ""
"La couche de vecteur de ligne de sortie s'est divisée à l'antiméridien."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3411
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:antimeridiansplit``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:antimeridiansplit``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3421
msgid "Geometry by expression"
msgstr "Géométrie par expression"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3422
msgid ""
"Updates existing geometries (or creates new geometries) for input features "
"by use of a QGIS expression."
msgstr ""
"Met à jour les géométries existantes (ou crée de nouvelles géométries) pour "
"les entités en entrée à l'aide d'une expression QGIS."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3425
msgid ""
"This allows complex geometry modifications which can utilize all the "
"flexibility of the QGIS expression engine to manipulate and create "
"geometries for output features."
msgstr ""
"Cela permet des modifications de géométrie complexes qui peuvent utiliser "
"toute la flexibilité du moteur d'expression QGIS pour manipuler et créer des"
" géométries pour les entités en sortie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3429
msgid ""
"For help with QGIS expression functions, see the inbuilt help available in "
"the :ref:`expression builder <vector_expressions>`."
msgstr ""
"Pour obtenir de l'aide sur les fonctions d'expression QGIS, consultez l'aide"
" intégrée disponible dans le :ref:`Constructeur d'expressions "
"<vector_expressions>`."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3448
msgid "**Output geometry type**"
msgstr "**Type de géométrie en sortie**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3449
msgid "``OUTPUT_GEOMETRY``"
msgstr "``OUTPUT_GEOMETRY``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3453
msgid ""
"The output geometry strongly depends on the expression: for instance, if you"
" create a buffer the geometry type has to be polygon. One of:"
msgstr ""
"La géométrie en sortie dépend fortement de l'expression: par exemple, si "
"vous créez un buffer, le type de géométrie doit être un polygone. Un des:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3458
msgid "0 --- Polygon"
msgstr "0 --- Polygone"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3459
msgid "1 --- Line"
msgstr "1 --- Ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3460
msgid "2 --- Point"
msgstr "2 --- Point"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3462
msgid "**Output geometry has z values**"
msgstr "**La géométrie de sortie a des valeurs z**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3463
msgid "``WITH_Z``"
msgstr "``WITH_Z``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3467
msgid "Choose if the output geometry should include the Z dimension"
msgstr "Choisissez si la géométrie de sortie doit inclure la dimension Z"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3468
msgid "**Output geometry has m values**"
msgstr "**La géométrie de sortie a valeurs m**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3469
msgid "``WITH_M``"
msgstr "``WITH_M``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3473
msgid "Choose if the output geometry should include the M dimension"
msgstr "Choisissez si la géométrie de sortie doit inclure la dimension M"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3474
msgid "**Geometry expression**"
msgstr "**Expression géométrique**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3475
msgid "``EXPRESSION``"
msgstr "``EXPRESSION``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3476
msgid "[expression]"
msgstr "[expression]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3478
msgid "Default: '$geometry'"
msgstr "Par défaut : '$geometry'"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3479
msgid ""
"Add the geometry expression you want to use. You can use the button to open "
"the Expression Dialog. The dialog lists all the relevant expressions, "
"together with their help and guide."
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez l'expression de géométrie que vous souhaitez utiliser. Vous pouvez "
"utiliser le bouton pour ouvrir la boîte de dialogue Expression. La boîte de "
"dialogue répertorie toutes les expressions pertinentes, ainsi que leur aide "
"et leur guide."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3483
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3506
msgid "**Modified geometry**"
msgstr "**Géométrie modifiée**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3514
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:geometrybyexpression``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:geometrybyexpression``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3524
msgid "Interpolate point on line"
msgstr "Interpoler le point sur la ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3525
msgid ""
"Creates a point geometry interpolated at a set distance along line or curve "
"geometries."
msgstr ""
"Crée une géométrie de point interpolée à une distance définie le long des "
"géométries de ligne ou de courbe."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3528
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3689
msgid "Z and M values are linearly interpolated from existing values."
msgstr ""
"Les valeurs Z et M sont interpolées linéairement à partir des valeurs "
"existantes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3530
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3691
msgid ""
"If a multipart geometry is encountered, only the first part is considered "
"when calculating the substring."
msgstr ""
"Si une géométrie en plusieurs parties est rencontrée, seule la première "
"partie est prise en compte lors du calcul de la sous-chaîne."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3533
msgid ""
"If the specified distance is greater than the input feature's length, the "
"resultant feature will have a null geometry."
msgstr ""
"Si la distance spécifiée est supérieure à la longueur de l'entité en entrée,"
" l'entité résultante aura une géométrie nulle."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3539
msgid "Interpolated point at 500m of the beginning of the line"
msgstr "Point interpolé à 500 m du début de la ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3541
msgid ":ref:`qgispointsalonglines`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgispointsalonglines`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3564
msgid "Distance from the beginning of the line"
msgstr "Distance depuis le début de la ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3565
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3588
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4703
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4726
msgid "**Interpolated points**"
msgstr "**Points interpolés**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3591
msgid ""
"The output point vector layer with features at a set distance along the line"
" or polygon boundary"
msgstr ""
"Couche vectorielle de point de sortie avec des entités à une distance "
"définie le long de la ligne ou de la limite du polygone"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3597
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:interpolatepoint``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:interpolatepoint``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3607
msgid "Keep N biggest parts"
msgstr "Gardez les N plus grandes parties"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3608
msgid ""
"Takes a layer with polygons or multipolygons and returns a new layer in "
"which only the *n* largest polygons of each multipolygon feature are kept. "
"If a feature has *n* or fewer parts, the feature will just be copied."
msgstr ""
"Prend une couche avec des polygones ou des multipolygones et renvoie une "
"nouvelle couche dans laquelle seuls les *n* plus grands polygones de chaque "
"entité multipolygone sont conservés. Si une entité comporte *n* ou moins de "
"parties, l'entité sera simplement copiée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3616
msgid ""
"Clockwise from top left: original multipart feature, one, two and three "
"biggest parts kept"
msgstr ""
"Dans le sens horaire à partir du haut à gauche: entité originale en "
"plusieurs parties, une, deux et trois plus grandes parties conservées"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3631
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3801
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3824
msgid "**Polygons**"
msgstr "**Polygones**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3635
msgid "**Parts to keep**"
msgstr "**Parties à conserver**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3636
msgid "``PARTS``"
msgstr "``PARTS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3637
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4138
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6456
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6876
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7041
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7397
msgid "[numeric: integer] |dataDefine|"
msgstr "[numérique: entier] |dataDefine|"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3640
msgid ""
"Number of parts to keep. If 1, only the biggest part of the feature will be "
"kept."
msgstr ""
"Nombre de parties à conserver. Si 1, seule la plus grande partie de l'entité"
" sera conservée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3642
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3665
msgid "**Parts**"
msgstr "**Les parties**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3668
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer with the N biggest parts of each feature"
msgstr ""
"La couche vectorielle de polygone en sortie avec les N plus grandes parties "
"de chaque entité"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3684
msgid "Line substring"
msgstr "Portion de ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3685
msgid ""
"Returns the portion of a line (or curve) which falls between the specified "
"start and end distances (measured from the beginning of the line)."
msgstr ""
"Renvoie la partie d'une ligne (ou courbe) qui se situe entre les distances "
"de début et de fin spécifiées (mesurées depuis le début de la ligne)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3697
msgid ""
"Substring line with starting distance set at 0 meters and the ending "
"distance at 250 meters."
msgstr ""
"Portion de Ligne avec une distance de départ fixée à 0 mètre et la distance "
"de fin à 250 mètres."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3703
msgid ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3726
msgid "Distance along the input line to the start point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distance le long de la ligne d'entrée jusqu'au point de départ de l'entité "
"de sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3732
msgid "Distance along the input line to the end point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distance le long de la ligne d'entrée jusqu'au point final de l'entité de "
"sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3733
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3756
msgid "**Substring**"
msgstr "**Portion**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3759
msgid "The output line vector layer."
msgstr "Couche de vecteur de ligne de sortie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3764
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:linesubstring``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:linesubstring``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3774
msgid "Lines to polygons"
msgstr "Lignes a polygones"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3775
msgid ""
"Generates a polygon layer using as polygon rings the lines from an input "
"line layer."
msgstr ""
"Génère une couche de polygones en utilisant comme polygone les lignes d'une "
"couche de lignes en entrée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3783
msgid ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3832
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:linestopolygons``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``qgis:linestopolygons``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3842
msgid "Merge lines"
msgstr "Fusionner des lignes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3843
msgid ""
"Joins all connected parts of MultiLineString geometries into single "
"LineString geometries."
msgstr ""
"Joint toutes les parties connectées des géométries MultiLineString en "
"géométries LineString uniques."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3846
msgid ""
"If any parts of the input MultiLineString geometries are not connected, the "
"resultant geometry will be a MultiLineString containing any lines which "
"could be merged and any non-connected line parts."
msgstr ""
"Si aucune partie des géométries MultiLineString en entrée n'est connectée, "
"la géométrie résultante sera une MultiLineString contenant toutes les lignes"
" qui pourraient être fusionnées et toutes les parties de ligne non "
"connectées."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3870
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3893
msgid "**Merged**"
msgstr "**Fusionné**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3896
msgid "The output (merged) line vector layer."
msgstr "Couche de vecteur de ligne de sortie (fusionnée)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3901
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:mergelines``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:mergelines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3911
msgid "Minimum bounding geometry"
msgstr "Géométrie d'emprise minimale"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3912
msgid ""
"Creates geometries which enclose the features from an input layer. The "
"features can be grouped by a field. The output layer will then contain one "
"feature per group value with a geometry (MBB) that covers the geometries of "
"the features with matching value."
msgstr ""
"Crée des géométries qui entourent les entités d'une couche d'entrée. Les "
"entités peuvent être regroupées par champ. La couche en sortie contiendra "
"alors une entité par valeur de groupe avec une géométrie (MBB) qui couvre "
"les géométries des entités avec une valeur correspondante."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3918
msgid "The following enclosing geometry types are supported:"
msgstr "Les types de géométrie englobants suivants sont pris en charge:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3920
msgid "bounding box (envelope)"
msgstr "Etendue  (enveloppe)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3921
msgid "oriented rectangle"
msgstr "rectangle orienté"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3922
msgid "circle"
msgstr "cercle"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3923
msgid "convex hull"
msgstr "enveloppe convexe"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3928
msgid ""
"Clockwise from top left: envelope, oriented rectangle, circle, convex hull"
msgstr ""
"Dans le sens horaire à partir du haut à gauche: enveloppe, rectangle "
"orienté, cercle, enveloppe convexe"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3931
msgid ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3949
msgid "**Field**"
msgstr "**Champ**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3954
msgid ""
"Features can be grouped by a field. If set, this causes the output layer to "
"contain one feature per grouped value with a minimal geometry covering only "
"the features with matching values."
msgstr ""
"Les entités peuvent être regroupées par champ. Si cette option est définie, "
"la couche de sortie contient une entité par valeur groupée avec une "
"géométrie minimale couvrant uniquement les entités avec des valeurs "
"correspondantes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3958
msgid "**Geometry type**"
msgstr "**Type de géométrie**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3963
msgid "Enclosing geometry types. One of:"
msgstr "Types de géométrie enveloppante. Un des:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3965
msgid "0 --- Envelope (Bounding Box)"
msgstr "0 --- Enveloppe (boîte englobante)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3966
msgid "1 --- Minimum Oriented Rectangle"
msgstr "1 --- Rectangle orienté minimum"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3967
msgid "2 --- Minimum Enclosing Circle"
msgstr "2 --- Cercle engloban minimum"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3968
msgid "3 --- Convex Hull"
msgstr "3 --- enveloppe convexe"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3970
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3993
msgid "**Bounding geometry**"
msgstr "**Géométrie englobante**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4009
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4019
msgid "Minimum enclosing circles"
msgstr "Cercles englobants minimum"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4020
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum enclosing circles of the features in the input layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcule le nombre minimum de cercles englobants des entités dans la couche "
"d'entrée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4026
msgid "Enclosing circles for each feature"
msgstr "Cercles fermés pour chaque entité"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4050
msgid "**Number of segments in circles**"
msgstr "**Nombre de segments dans les cercles**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4054
msgid "Default: 72"
msgstr "Par défaut : 72"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4057
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4080
msgid "**Minimum enclosing circles**"
msgstr "**Cercles englobants minimum**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4091
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4101
msgid "Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)"
msgstr "Buffer multi-anneaux (distance constante)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4102
msgid ""
"Computes multi-ring (*donut*) buffer for the features of the input layer, "
"using a fixed or dynamic distance and number of rings."
msgstr ""
"Calcule un buffer à anneaux multiples (*donut*) pour les caractéristiques de"
" la couche d'entrée, en utilisant une distance et un nombre d'anneaux fixes "
"ou dynamiques."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4108
msgid "Multi-ring buffer for a line, point and polygon layer"
msgstr ""
"Buffer multi-anneaux pour une couche de lignes, de points et de polygones"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4117
msgid ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4136
msgid "**Number of rings**"
msgstr "**Nombre d'anneaux**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4137
msgid "``RINGS``"
msgstr "``RINGS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4141
msgid ""
"The number of rings. It can be a unique value (same number of rings for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the number of rings "
"depends on feature values)."
msgstr ""
"Le nombre d anneaux. Il peut s'agir d'une valeur unique (même nombre "
"d'anneaux pour toutes les entités) ou elle peut être extraite des données "
"d'entités (le nombre d'anneaux dépend des valeurs des entités)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4145
msgid "**Distance between rings**"
msgstr "**Distance entre les anneaux**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4150
msgid ""
"Distance between the rings. It can be a unique value (same distance for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the distance depends on"
" feature values)."
msgstr ""
"Distance entre les anneaux. Il peut s'agir d'une valeur unique (même "
"distance pour toutes les entités) ou elle peut être extraite des données "
"d'entités (la distance dépend des valeurs d'entités)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4154
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4177
msgid "**Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)**"
msgstr "**Buffer multi-anneaux (distance constante)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4187
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4197
msgid "Multipart to singleparts"
msgstr "Multipartie  vers monopartie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4198
msgid "Splits multipart features in the input layer into singlepart features."
msgstr ""
"Divise les entités à plusieurs parties de la couche d'entrée en entités à "
"partie unique"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4201
msgid ""
"The attributes of the output layer are the same as the original ones but "
"divided into single features."
msgstr ""
"Les attributs de la couche de sortie sont les mêmes que ceux d'origine mais "
"divisés en entités uniques."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4207
msgid ""
"Left the multipart source layer and right the single part output result"
msgstr ""
"A gauche la couche source en plusieurs parties et à droite le résultat en "
"partie unique"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4219
msgid ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4237
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4260
msgid "**Single parts**"
msgstr "**Monoparties**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4263
msgid "The output vector layer."
msgstr "La couche de vecteur de sortie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4268
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4278
msgid "Offset lines"
msgstr "Lignes décalées"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4279
msgid ""
"Offsets lines by a specified distance. Positive distances will offset lines "
"to the left, and negative distances will offset them to the right."
msgstr ""
"Décale les lignes d'une distance spécifiée. Les distances positives décalent"
" les lignes vers la gauche et les distances négatives les décalent vers la "
"droite."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4286
msgid "In blue the source layer, in red the offset one"
msgstr "En bleu la couche source, en rouge celui décalé"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4292
msgid ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4316
msgid ""
"Offset distance. You can use the Data Defined button on the right to choose "
"a field from which the radius will be calculated. This way you can have "
"different radius for each feature (see :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."
msgstr ""
"Distance de décalage. Vous pouvez utiliser le bouton Données définies à "
"droite pour choisir un champ à partir duquel le rayon sera calculé. De cette"
" façon, vous pouvez avoir un rayon différent pour chaque entité (voir "
":ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4325
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6323
msgid "Default: 8"
msgstr "Par défaut : 8"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4388
msgid "Output (offset) line layer"
msgstr "Couche de ligne de sortie (offset)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4393
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:offsetline``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:offsetline``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4403
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4413
msgid "Oriented minimum bounding box"
msgstr "Boîte de délimitation minimale orientée"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4404
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum area rotated rectangle for each feature in the input "
"layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcule la surface minimale pivotée du rectangle pour chaque entité de la "
"couche d'entrée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4437
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4460
msgid "**Bounding boxes**"
msgstr "**Etendues**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4471
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4481
msgid "Orthogonalize"
msgstr "Orthogonaliser"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4482
msgid ""
"Attempts to orthogonalize the geometries of the input line or polygon layer."
" This process shifts the vertices in the geometries to try to make every "
"angle in the geometry either a right angle or a straight line."
msgstr ""
"Tente d'orthogonaliser les géométries de la ligne d'entrée ou de la couche "
"de polygones. Ce processus décale les sommets des géométries pour essayer de"
" faire de chaque angle de la géométrie soit un angle droit soit une ligne "
"droite."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4490
msgid "In blue the source layer and in the red orthogonalized result"
msgstr "En bleu la couche source et en rouge le résultat orthogonalisé"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4513
msgid "**Maximum angle tolerance (degrees)**"
msgstr "**Tolérance d'angle maximale (degrés)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4514
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4604
msgid "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"
msgstr "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4518
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum deviation from a right angle or straight line a vertex "
"can have for it to be adjusted. Smaller tolerances mean that only vertices "
"which are already closer to right angles will be adjusted, and larger "
"tolerances mean that vertices which deviate further from right angles will "
"also be adjusted."
msgstr ""
"Spécifiez l'écart maximal par rapport à un angle droit ou à une ligne droite"
" qu'un sommet peut avoir pour qu'il soit ajusté. Des tolérances plus petites"
" signifient que seuls les sommets qui sont déjà plus proches des angles "
"droits seront ajustés, et des tolérances plus grandes signifient que les "
"sommets qui s'écartent davantage des angles droits seront également ajustés."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4524
msgid "**Maximum algorithm iterations**"
msgstr "**Nombre maximal d'itérations de l'algorithme**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4525
msgid "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"
msgstr "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4528
msgid "Default: 1000"
msgstr "Par défaut : 1000"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4529
msgid ""
"Setting a larger number for the maximum number of iterations will result in "
"a more orthogonal geometry at the cost of extra processing time."
msgstr ""
"La définition d'un nombre plus élevé pour le nombre maximal d'itérations se "
"traduira par une géométrie plus orthogonale au prix d'un temps de traitement"
" supplémentaire."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4532
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4555
msgid "**Orthogonalized**"
msgstr "**Orthogonalisé**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4558
msgid "The output polygon vector layer with adjusted angles."
msgstr "Couche vectorielle de polygone en sortie avec angles ajustés."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4563
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orthogonalize``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:orthogonalize``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4573
msgid "Point on Surface"
msgstr "Point sur la surface"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4574
msgid ""
"For each feature of the input layer, returns a point that is guaranteed to "
"lie on the surface of the feature geometry."
msgstr ""
"Pour chaque entité de la couche en entrée, renvoie un point qui est garanti "
"se trouver sur la surface de la géométrie de l'entité."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4585
msgid ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4603
msgid "**Create point on surface for each part**"
msgstr "**Créer un point sur la surface pour chaque partie**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4606
msgid "If checked, a point will be created for each part of the geometry."
msgstr ""
"Si cette case est cochée, un point sera créé pour chaque partie de la "
"géométrie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4607
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4630
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4870
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4893
msgid "**Point**"
msgstr "**Point**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4633
msgid "The output point vector layer."
msgstr "Couche vectorielle du point de sortie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4638
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointonsurface``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:pointonsurface``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4648
msgid "Points along geometry"
msgstr "Points le long de la géométrie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4649
msgid ""
"Creates points at regular intervals along line or polygon geometries. "
"Created points will have new attributes added for the distance along the "
"geometry and the angle of the line at the point."
msgstr ""
"Crée des points à intervalles réguliers le long des géométries de ligne ou "
"de polygone. Les points créés auront de nouveaux attributs ajoutés pour la "
"distance le long de la géométrie et l'angle de la ligne au point."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4653
msgid ""
"An optional start and end offset can be specified, which controls how far "
"from the start and end of the geometry the points should be created."
msgstr ""
"Un décalage de début et de fin facultatif peut être spécifié, qui contrôle "
"la distance entre le début et la fin de la géométrie, les points doivent "
"être créés."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4660
msgid "Points created along the source line layer"
msgstr "Points créés le long de la couche linéaire source"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4665
msgid ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4688
msgid "Distance between two consecutive points along the line"
msgstr "Distance entre deux points consécutifs le long de la ligne"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4689
msgid "**Start offset**"
msgstr "**Décalage de début**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4690
msgid "``START_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``START_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4694
msgid ""
"Distance from the beginning of the input line, representing the position of "
"the first point."
msgstr ""
"Distance depuis le début de la ligne d'entrée, représentant la position du "
"premier point."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4696
msgid "**End offset**"
msgstr "**Décalage de fin**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4697
msgid "``END_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``END_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4738
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointsalonglines``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:pointsalonglines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4748
msgid "Points displacement"
msgstr "Déplacement des points"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4749
msgid ""
"Given a distance of proximity, identifies nearby point features and radially"
" distributes them over a circle whose center represents their barycenter. A "
"convenient tool to scatter overlaid features."
msgstr ""
"Étant donné une distance de proximité, identifie les entités ponctuelles "
"proches et les répartit radialement sur un cercle dont le centre représente "
"leur barycentre. Un outil pratique pour disperser les fonctionnalités "
"superposées."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4770
msgid "**Minimum distance to other points**"
msgstr "**Distance minimale à d'autres points**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4771
msgid "``PROXIMITY``"
msgstr "``PROXIMITY``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4775
msgid ""
"Distance below which point features are considered close. Close features are"
" distributed altogether."
msgstr ""
"Distance en dessous de laquelle les entités ponctuelles sont considérées "
"comme proches. Les entités proches sont entièrement distribuées."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4778
msgid "**Displacement distance**"
msgstr "**Distance de déplacement**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4783
msgid "Radius of the circle on which close features are placed"
msgstr "Rayon du cercle sur lequel les entités proches sont placées"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4784
msgid "**Horizontal distribution for two point case**"
msgstr "**Distribution horizontale pour cas à deux points**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4785
msgid "``HORIZONTAL``"
msgstr "``HORIZONTAL``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4789
msgid ""
"When only two points are identified as close, aligns them horizontally on "
"the circle instead of vertically."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque seuls deux points sont identifiés comme proches, les alignent "
"horizontalement sur le cercle plutôt que verticalement."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4792
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4815
msgid "**Displaced**"
msgstr "**Déplacé**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4818
msgid "Output point vector layer"
msgstr "Couche vectorielle de point de sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4823
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4833
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4846
msgid "Pole of inaccessibility"
msgstr "Pôle d'inaccessibilité"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4834
msgid ""
"Calculates the pole of inaccessibility for a polygon layer, which is the "
"most distant internal point from the boundary of the surface."
msgstr ""
"Calcule le pôle d'inaccessibilité pour une couche de polygones, qui est le "
"point interne le plus éloigné de la limite de la surface."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4837
msgid ""
"This algorithm uses the 'polylabel' algorithm (Vladimir Agafonkin, 2016), "
"which is an iterative approach guaranteed to find the true pole of "
"inaccessibility within a specified tolerance. A more precise tolerance "
"(lower value) requires more iterations and will take longer to calculate."
msgstr ""
"Cet algorithme utilise l'algorithme ``polylabel`` (Vladimir Agafonkin, "
"2016), qui est une approche itérative garantie pour trouver le véritable "
"pôle d'inaccessibilité dans une tolérance spécifiée. Une tolérance plus "
"précise (valeur inférieure) nécessite plus d'itérations et prendra plus de "
"temps à calculer."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4869
msgid "Set the tolerance for the calculation"
msgstr "Définit la tolérance pour le calcul"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4903
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4913
msgid "Polygonize"
msgstr "Transformer en polygone"

