#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6173
msgid "Simplify"
msgstr "Simplifier"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6174
msgid ""
"Simplifies the geometries in a line or polygon layer. It creates a new layer"
" with the same features as the ones in the input layer, but with geometries "
"containing a lower number of vertices."
msgstr ""
"Simplifie les géométries d'une couche de lignes ou de polygones. Il crée une"
" nouvelle couche avec les mêmes caractéristiques que celles de la couche "
"d'entrée, mais avec des géométries contenant un nombre de vertex inférieur."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6178
msgid ""
"The algorithm gives a choice of simplification methods, including distance "
"based (the \"Douglas-Peucker\" algorithm), area based (\"Visvalingam\" "
"algorithm) and snapping geometries to grid."
msgstr ""
"L'algorithme offre un choix de méthodes de simplification, notamment la "
"distance (l'algorithme \"Douglas-Peucker\"), la zone (l'algorithme "
"\"Visvalingam\") et l'alignement des géométries sur la grille."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6192
msgid ""
":ref:`qgiscoveragesimplify`, :ref:`qgissmoothgeometry`, "
":ref:`qgisdensifygeometries`, :ref:`qgisdensifygeometriesgivenaninterval`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgiscoveragesimplify`, :ref:`qgissmoothgeometry`, "
":ref:`qgisdensifygeometries`, :ref:`qgisdensifygeometriesgivenaninterval`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6211
msgid "**Simplification method**"
msgstr "**Méthode de simplification**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6216
msgid "Simplification method. One of:"
msgstr "Méthode de simplification. Un des:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6218
msgid "0 --- Distance (Douglas-Peucker)"
msgstr "0 --- Distance (Douglas-Peucker)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6219
msgid "1 --- Snap to grid"
msgstr "1 --- Accrocher à la grille"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6220
msgid "2 --- Area (Visvalingam)"
msgstr "2 --- Surface (Visvalingam)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6227
msgid ""
"Threshold tolerance (in units of the layer): if the distance between two "
"nodes is smaller than the tolerance value, the segment will be simplified "
"and vertices will be removed."
msgstr ""
"Tolérance de seuil (en unités de la couche): si la distance entre deux nœuds"
" est inférieure à la valeur de tolérance, le segment sera simplifié et les "
"sommets seront supprimés."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6231
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6255
msgid "**Simplified**"
msgstr "**Simplifié**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6258
msgid "The output (simplified) vector layer"
msgstr "La couche vectorielle de sortie (simplifiée)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6263
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:simplifygeometries``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:simplifygeometries``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6273
msgid "Single sided buffer"
msgstr "Zone tampon simple face"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6274
msgid ""
"Computes a buffer on lines by a specified distance on one side of the line "
"only."
msgstr ""
"Calcule un buffer sur les lignes d'une distance spécifiée d'un côté de la "
"ligne uniquement."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6277
msgid "Buffer always results in a polygon layer."
msgstr "Le buffer produit toujours une couche polygonale."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6282
msgid "Left versus right side buffer on the same vector line layer"
msgstr "Tampon gauche ou droit sur la même couche de lignes vectorielles"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6284
msgid ":ref:`qgisbuffer`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisbuffer`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6307
msgid "Buffer distance."
msgstr "Distance buffer."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6308
msgid "**Side**"
msgstr "**Côté**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6309
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7217
msgid "``SIDE``"
msgstr "``SIDE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6313
msgid "Which side to create the buffer on. One of:"
msgstr "De quel côté créer le buffer. Un des:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6316
msgid "0 -- Left"
msgstr "0 - Gauche"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6317
msgid "1 -- Right"
msgstr "1 - Droite"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6359
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6383
msgid "**Buffer**"
msgstr "**Zone tampon**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6391
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:singlesidedbuffer``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:singlesidedbuffer``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6401
msgid "Smooth"
msgstr "Lisser"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6402
msgid ""
"Smooths the geometries in a line or polygon layer by adding more **vertices "
"and corners** to the feature geometries."
msgstr ""
"Lisse les géométries d'une couche de lignes ou de polygones en ajoutant plus"
" de **vertex et coins** aux géométries d'entités."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6405
msgid ""
"The iterations parameter dictates how many smoothing iterations will be "
"applied to each geometry. A higher number of iterations results in smoother "
"geometries with the cost of greater number of nodes in the geometries."
msgstr ""
"Le paramètre d'itérations détermine le nombre d'itérations de lissage qui "
"seront appliquées à chaque géométrie. Un nombre d'itérations plus élevé se "
"traduit par des géométries plus lisses avec le coût d'un plus grand nombre "
"de nœuds dans les géométries."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6413
msgid "Increasing number of iterations causes smoother geometries"
msgstr ""
"L'augmentation du nombre d'itérations entraîne des géométries plus lisses"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6415
msgid ""
"The offset parameter controls how \"tightly\" the smoothed geometries follow"
" the original geometries. Smaller values results in a tighter fit, and "
"larger values will create a looser fit."
msgstr ""
"Le paramètre de décalage contrôle le degré de \"serrage\" des géométries "
"lissées par rapport aux géométries d'origine. Des valeurs plus petites "
"entraînent un ajustement plus serré, et des valeurs plus grandes créeront un"
" ajustement plus lâche."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6422
msgid ""
"Blue: the input layer. Offset 0.25 gives the red line, while offset 0.50 "
"gives the green line."
msgstr ""
"Bleu: la couche d'entrée. Le décalage 0,25 donne la ligne rouge, tandis que "
"le décalage 0,50 donne la ligne verte."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6425
msgid ""
"The maximum angle parameter can be used to prevent smoothing of nodes with "
"large angles. Any node where the angle of the segments to either side is "
"larger than this will not be smoothed. For example, setting the maximum "
"angle to 90 degrees or lower would preserve right angles in the geometry."
msgstr ""
"Le paramètre d'angle maximal peut être utilisé pour empêcher le lissage des "
"nœuds avec de grands angles. Tout nœud dont l'angle des segments de chaque "
"côté est supérieur à celui-ci ne sera pas lissé. Par exemple, si vous "
"définissez l'angle maximum à 90 degrés ou moins, les angles droits de la "
"géométrie seront préservés."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6435
msgid ""
":ref:`qgissimplifygeometries`, :ref:`qgiscoveragesimplify`, "
":ref:`qgisdensifygeometries`, :ref:`qgisdensifygeometriesgivenaninterval`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgissimplifygeometries`, :ref:`qgiscoveragesimplify`, "
":ref:`qgisdensifygeometries`, :ref:`qgisdensifygeometriesgivenaninterval`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6454
msgid "**Iterations**"
msgstr "**Itérations**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6455
msgid "``ITERATIONS``"
msgstr "``ITERATIONS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6459
msgid ""
"Increasing the number of iterations will give smoother geometries (and more "
"vertices)."
msgstr ""
"L'augmentation du nombre d'itérations donnera des géométries plus lisses (et"
" plus de vertex)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6465
msgid "Default: 0.25"
msgstr "Par défaut : 0.25"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6466
msgid ""
"Increasing values will *move* the smoothed lines / boundaries further away "
"from the input lines / boundaries."
msgstr ""
"Des valeurs croissantes *déplaceront* les lignes / limites lissées plus loin"
" des lignes / limites d'entrée."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6468
msgid "**Maximum node angle to smooth**"
msgstr "**Angle de nœud maximum pour lisser**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6469
msgid "``MAX_ANGLE``"
msgstr "``MAX_ANGLE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6472
msgid "Default: 180.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 180.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6473
msgid "Every node below this value will be smoothed"
msgstr "Chaque nœud en dessous de cette valeur sera lissé"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6474
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6498
msgid "**Smoothed**"
msgstr "**Lissé**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6501
msgid "Output (smoothed) vector layer"
msgstr "Couche vectorielle de sortie (lissée)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6506
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:smoothgeometry``"
msgstr "**ID de l'algorithme** : ``native:smoothgeometry``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6516
msgid "Snap geometries to layer"
msgstr "Accrochage des géométries à la couche"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6517
msgid ""
"Snaps the geometries in a layer either to the geometries from another layer,"
" or to geometries within the same layer."
msgstr ""
"Accroche les géométries d'une couche aux géométries d'une autre couche ou "
"aux géométries de la même couche."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6520
msgid ""
"Matching is done based on a tolerance distance, and vertices will be "
"inserted or removed as required to make the geometries match the reference "
"geometries."
msgstr ""
"La correspondance est effectuée sur la base d'une distance de tolérance, et "
"les sommets seront insérés ou supprimés selon les besoins pour que les "
"géométries correspondent aux géométries de référence."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6528
msgid ":ref:`qgissnappointstogrid`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgissnappointstogrid`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6546
msgid "**Reference layer**"
msgstr "**Couche de référence**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6547
msgid "``REFERENCE_LAYER``"
msgstr "``REFERENCE_LAYER``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6549
msgid "Vector layer to snap to"
msgstr "Couche de vecteur à accrocher"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6555
msgid ""
"Control how close input vertices need to be to the reference layer "
"geometries before they are snapped."
msgstr ""
"Contrôlez la distance entre les sommets en entrée et les géométries de la "
"couche de référence avant leur accrochage."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6557
msgid "**Behavior**"
msgstr "**Comportement**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6558
msgid "``BEHAVIOR``"
msgstr "``BEHAVIOR``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6562
msgid ""
"Snapping can be done to an existing node or a segment (its closest point to "
"the vertex to move). Available snapping options:"
msgstr ""
"La capture peut être effectuée sur un nœud ou un segment existant (son point"
" le plus proche du sommet à déplacer). Options de capture disponibles:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6566
msgid "0 --- Prefer aligning nodes, insert extra vertices where required"
msgstr ""
"0 --- Préférez l'alignement des nœuds, insérez des sommets supplémentaires "
"si nécessaire"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6573
msgid "1 --- Prefer closest point, insert extra vertices where required"
msgstr ""
"1 --- Préférez le point le plus proche, insérez des sommets supplémentaires "
"si nécessaire"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6580
msgid "2 --- Prefer aligning nodes, don't insert new vertices"
msgstr ""
